{"parse":{"title":"S. K. Sama","pageid":48552239,"revid":857624985,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n\n</p>\n<table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">S. K. Sama</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<span class=\"nickname\">Surinder Kumar Sama</span><br />1934 (age&#160;83&#8211;84)<br /><span class=\"birthplace\">India</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Occupation</th><td class=\"role\">\nGastroentrologist</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Known&#160;for</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Endocrinology\" title=\"Endocrinology\">Endocrinology</a><br /><a href=\"/wiki/Diabetology\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Diabetology\">Diabetology</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Awards</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Padma_Shri\" title=\"Padma Shri\">Padma Shri</a><br /><a href=\"/wiki/Dr._B._C._Roy_Award\" title=\"Dr. B. C. Roy Award\">Dr. B. C. Roy Award</a><br />IAPC Lifetime Achievement Award<br /><a href=\"/wiki/Punjab_Rattan_Award\" title=\"Punjab Rattan Award\">Punjab Rattan Award</a><br />DMA Ratna Award<br />Bharat Jyoti Award<br />Bhaskar Award<br />Human Care Award<br />Delhi Rattan Award</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Surinder Kumar Sama</b> (born 1934) is an Indian <a href=\"/wiki/Gastroenterologist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gastroenterologist\">gastroenterologist</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Doctor_Profile_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Doctor_Profile-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> known for his expertise in <a href=\"/wiki/Endocrinology\" title=\"Endocrinology\">endocrinology</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Diabetology\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Diabetology\">diabetology</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dr._Surender_Kumar,_Endocrinologist,_Delhi_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dr._Surender_Kumar,_Endocrinologist,_Delhi-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He is considered by many as the <i>Father of Gastroenterolgy</i> in India.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Area_of_Expertise_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Area_of_Expertise-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The discovery of <a href=\"/wiki/Non-cirrhotic_portal_fibrosis\" title=\"Non-cirrhotic portal fibrosis\">Non-cirrhotic portal fibrosis</a>, an <a href=\"/wiki/Idiopathic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Idiopathic\">idiopathic</a> chronic liver disease is attributed to him,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Credihealth_profile_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Credihealth_profile-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> which he described in a 1962 medical paper, co-authored with Ramalingaswami and Wig.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ultrastructure_of_the_liver_in_non-cirrhotic_portal_fibrosis_with_portal_hypertension_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ultrastructure_of_the_liver_in_non-cirrhotic_portal_fibrosis_with_portal_hypertension-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The Government of India awarded him the civilian honour of the <a href=\"/wiki/Padma_Shri\" title=\"Padma Shri\">Padma Shri</a> in 2004 for his pioneering research on liver diseases including Non-cirrhotic portal fibrosis and <a href=\"/wiki/Hepatitis_B\" title=\"Hepatitis B\">Hepatitis B</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Doctor_gets_Padma_Shri_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Doctor_gets_Padma_Shri-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Padma_Awards_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Padma_Awards-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Sama also received the highest Indian medical honour of <a href=\"/wiki/Dr._B._C._Roy_Award\" title=\"Dr. B. C. Roy Award\">Dr. B. C. Roy Award</a> in 2004.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dr._B.C._Roy_awards_presented_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dr._B.C._Roy_awards_presented-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">Biography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=S._K._Sama&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Biography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Sama was born in 1934, did his graduate studies at the <a href=\"/wiki/All_India_Institute_of_Medical_Sciences_Delhi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"All India Institute of Medical Sciences Delhi\">All India Institute of Medical Sciences Delhi</a> and started his career by joining his alma mater, in 1958.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Area_of_Expertise_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Area_of_Expertise-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> He stayed at AIIMS till 1974 during which time he established the Department of Gastroenterology at the institute as well as at G. B. Pant Hospital, another government hospital in the Indian capital city. In 1976, he joined <a href=\"/wiki/Sir_Ganga_Ram_Hospital_(India)\" title=\"Sir Ganga Ram Hospital (India)\">Sir Ganga Ram Hospital</a> as an honorary physician of gastroenterology and served the charitable hospital for 36 years, including as its chairman from 1995 to 2006.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> During this period, he founded the Gastroenterology department there which has now grown to become a centre of excellence. He held various posts at the hospital, including that of the founder member of the Board of Management.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Area_of_Expertise_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Area_of_Expertise-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> He retains the Management Board membership and is also a member of its Board of Trustees.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Administration_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Administration-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> While continuing his association with Sir Ganga Ram Hospital, he founded Sama Hospital in 1982<sup id=\"cite_ref-About_Us_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-About_Us-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> and is its director.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Management_Team_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Management_Team-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Sama is considered by many as a pioneer of medical research on liver diseases in India.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Area_of_Expertise_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Area_of_Expertise-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> His 1962 article is reported to be the first attempt at describing the chronic disease of <a href=\"/wiki/Non-cirrhotic_portal_fibrosis\" title=\"Non-cirrhotic portal fibrosis\">Non-cirrhotic portal fibrosis</a> and is also credited with recognised research on <a href=\"/wiki/Hepatitis_B\" title=\"Hepatitis B\">Hepatitis B</a>. His researches have been documented by over 45 articles, published in peer reviewed national and international journals.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Noncirrhotic_portal_fibrosis_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Noncirrhotic_portal_fibrosis-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Conditional_overexpression_of_insulin-like_growth_factor-1_enhances_hippocampal_neurogenesis_and_restores_immature_neuron_dendritic_processes_after_traumatic_brain_injury_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Conditional_overexpression_of_insulin-like_growth_factor-1_enhances_hippocampal_neurogenesis_and_restores_immature_neuron_dendritic_processes_after_traumatic_brain_injury-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> He is a former president and a life member of the Indian Society of Gastroenterology and has organised six therapeutic endoscopic workshops during his tenure there.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Area_of_Expertise_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Area_of_Expertise-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> He is also a life member of the Indian Society of Study of Liver Disease, Indian Society of Gastrointestinal Endoscopy, American Gastroenterology Association and Association of Physicians of India and was the president of the New Delhi chapter of the <a href=\"/wiki/Indian_Medical_Association\" title=\"Indian Medical Association\">Indian Medical Association</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Area_of_Expertise_3-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Area_of_Expertise-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> He sits in the Board of Advisors of the American Hospital Management Company and served as the personal physician to the President of India in 2001.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology_9-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> He is also the vice president of the Managing Committee of DAV College.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Office_Bearers_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Office_Bearers-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> He has delivered several award lectures such as Presidential Oration (1986), Dr. B. L. Kapur Memorial Oration (1991), Dr. K. L. Wig Memorial Oration (2002) and Dr. R. S. Tiwary Oration (2005).<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology_9-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Sama, a Fellow of the <a href=\"/wiki/World_Health_Organization\" title=\"World Health Organization\">World Health Organization</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-S._K._Sama_VLCC_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-S._K._Sama_VLCC-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> and the <a href=\"/wiki/National_Academy_of_Medical_Sciences\" title=\"National Academy of Medical Sciences\">National Academy of Medical Sciences</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-List_of_Fellows_-_NAMS_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-List_of_Fellows_-_NAMS-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup> received <a href=\"/wiki/Dr._B._C._Roy_Award\" title=\"Dr. B. C. Roy Award\">Dr. B. C. Roy Award</a>, the highest Indian award in the medical category, from the <a href=\"/wiki/Medical_Council_of_India\" title=\"Medical Council of India\">Medical Council of India</a> in 2004.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dr._B.C._Roy_awards_presented_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dr._B.C._Roy_awards_presented-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> The Government of India awarded him the civilian honour of the <a href=\"/wiki/Padma_Shri\" title=\"Padma Shri\">Padma Shri</a> in 2004<sup id=\"cite_ref-Padma_Awards_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Padma_Awards-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> and the International Association for Preventive Cardiology honoured him with their Lifetime Achievement Award in 2006.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology_9-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> He is also a recipient of several other awards such as <a href=\"/wiki/Punjab_Rattan_Award\" title=\"Punjab Rattan Award\">Punjab Rattan Award</a>, DMA Ratna Award, Bharat Jyoti Award, Bhaskar Award, Human Care Award and Delhi Rattan Award.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology_9-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dr._S.K._Sama,_MD,_DM_Gastroenterology-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_articles\">Selected articles</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=S._K._Sama&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Selected articles\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation journal\">B. N. Tandon; R. Lakshminarayanan; S. Bhargava; N. C. Nayak; S. K. SAMA (1970). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1553129\">\"Ultrastructure of the liver in non-cirrhotic portal fibrosis with portal hypertension\"</a>. <i>Gut</i>. <b>11</b> (905\u2013910). <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1136/gut.11.11.905\">10.1136/gut.11.11.905</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Central\" title=\"PubMed Central\">PMC</a>&#160;<span class=\"plainlinks\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1553129\">1553129</a>&#8239;<img alt=\"Freely accessible\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Lock-green.svg/9px-Lock-green.svg.png\" title=\"Freely accessible\" width=\"9\" height=\"14\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Lock-green.svg/14px-Lock-green.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Lock-green.svg/18px-Lock-green.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"813\" /></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Gut&amp;rft.atitle=Ultrastructure+of+the+liver+in+non-cirrhotic+portal+fibrosis+with+portal+hypertension&amp;rft.volume=11&amp;rft.issue=905%E2%80%93910&amp;rft.date=1970&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC1553129&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1136%2Fgut.11.11.905&amp;rft.au=B.+N.+Tandon&amp;rft.au=R.+Lakshminarayanan&amp;rft.au=S.+Bhargava&amp;rft.au=N.+C.+Nayak&amp;rft.au=S.+K.+SAMA&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC1553129&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AS.+K.+Sama\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation journal\">S.K. Sama; S. Bhargava; N. Gopi Nath; J. R. Talwar; N. C. Nayak; B.N. Tandon; K. L. Wig (August 1971). \"Noncirrhotic portal fibrosis\". <i>American Journal of Medicine</i>. <b>51</b> (2): 160\u2013169. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1016/0002-9343%2871%2990234-8\">10.1016/0002-9343(71)90234-8</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft